about.description:
GeofileOps is a library to make spatial operations on large geo files fast
and easy. Accomplishes this by using spatialite, geopandas and gdal under
the hood to perform geospatial operations on files by using all available
CPU cores.
about.summary: Package to do spatial operations on large geo files.

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "geofileops" %}
{% set version = "0.6.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/geofileops-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 44326b204398675a901635718401e41277d392ae0307134e8a94076226756edd

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.8
  run:
    - cloudpickle
    - fiona
    - gdal
    - geopandas >=0.11
    - libspatialite >=5.0
    - numpy
    - pandas
    - psutil
    - pygeos
    - pyogrio
    - pyproj
    - python >=3.8
    - shapely
    - topojson
    
test:
  imports:
    - geofileops
    - geofileops.util
  requires:
    - pytest
  source_files:
    - tests
  commands:
    - pytest tests
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/geofileops/geofileops
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Package to do spatial operations on large geo files.
  description: |
    GeofileOps is a library to make spatial operations on large geo files fast  
    and easy. Accomplishes this by using spatialite, geopandas and gdal under  
    the hood to perform geospatial operations on files by using all available 
    CPU cores.
  doc_url: https://geofileops.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/geofileops/geofileops/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - theroggy
